        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Policy: add agent workspace conformance checks",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAdds a policy-only conformance surface for locking agent workspace posture down to read-only/no-write configurations.\n\n- records agent/default sandbox `workspaceAccess` as policy evidence\n- adds `agents.workspace.allowedAccess` and `agents.workspace.denyTools` checks\n- documents the supported read-only policy shape and evidence payload\n\nThis is stacked after #81981 and intentionally stays at config/policy conformance level; it does not add runtime enforcement.\n\n## Policy syntax\n\n```jsonc\n{\n  \"agents\": {\n    \"workspace\": {\n      \"allowedAccess\": [\"none\", \"ro\"],\n      \"denyTools\": [\"exec\", \"process\", \"write\", \"edit\", \"apply_patch\"],\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\n## Verification\n\n- `git diff --check`\n- `pnpm docs:list`\n- `node scripts/check-deadcode-unused-files.mjs`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/policy/src/doctor/register.test.ts extensions/policy/src/cli.test.ts --run --reporter=dot`\n- `node node_modules/@typescript/native-preview/bin/tsgo.js -p test/tsconfig/tsconfig.extensions.test.json --incremental --tsBuildInfoFile .artifacts/tsgo-cache/extensions-test-policy-agent-workspace-final.tsbuildinfo`\n- `/mnt/c/src/claws-hapi/.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local --reviewer codex --fallback-reviewer none`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Policy conformance can now require agent sandbox workspace access to stay within an allowlist and require explicit deny coverage for shell/process/file-mutation tools.\nReal environment tested: WSL checkout at `/root/src/openclaw-policy-agent-workspace` on Ubuntu-24.04.\nExact steps or command run after this patch: Ran focused policy doctor/CLI tests, extension test typecheck, docs listing, deadcode unused-file check, diff whitespace check, and Codex autoreview from the WSL checkout.\nEvidence after fix: 115 focused policy tests passed; extension test typecheck completed successfully; docs list completed successfully; deadcode unused-file check passed; autoreview completed with no accepted/actionable findings after fixing its one accepted finding.\nObserved result after fix: Malformed agent workspace policy reports policy shape errors, nonconforming workspace/tool posture reports policy findings, and read-only policy with group deny coverage is accepted.\nWhat was not tested: No runtime sandbox/tool enforcement was tested because this PR only adds config-level policy conformance.\r\n\n",
